        "subtitle": "The Japanese Utility Knife",
        "intro_content": "<p>The <strong>bunka knife</strong> is a versatile Japanese <strong>kitchen knife</strong> with a distinctive k-tip (reverse tanto point) that excels at precision work. Less common in Australia than the santoku or gyuto, the bunka knife offers the same all-purpose functionality with added control for detail cuts. The angular tip pierces ingredients cleanly and handles tasks that round-tipped knives struggle with. XinZuo bunka knives feature 67-layer Damascus steel forged in Yangjiang, combining traditional Japanese blade geometry with modern metallurgy. If you want one knife that handles vegetables, proteins, and precision work equally well, the bunka is a serious contender.</p>",
